work_experience.description: As an Administrator Oracle BI Publisher, you will be working for our client, a Polish leader in the energy sector, supporting the development and maintenance of their Oracle Analytics Publisher system. This project focuses on delivering IT services for operational and analytical reporting, involving tasks such as system analysis, design, programming, and documentation preparation. The project's goal is to enable seamless IT support for two primary instances of the system.
Worked on a large scale financial system with high availability and resilience. Been responsible for designing and implementing scalable and maintainable architectures.
Developed e-commerce applications using React.js. Implemented responsive and user-friendly interfaces. Worked closely with the design team to create pixel-perfect layouts.

projects.name: SmartGardener
projects.description: A fullstack web application for managing your plants. Implemented with React.js and Node.js. Features include plant database, watering reminders, and plant care tips. Deployed on Heroku. Offers rich UI/UX experience.

projects.name: CI/CD Pipeline
projects.description: Implemented complete CI/CD pipeline for a web application.

projects.name: HomeFinApp
projects.description: A web application for managing personal finances. Features include budget tracking, expense categorization, financial reports, analyzing receipts, and setting financial goals. WIP.

cv.about_me: John Doe is a Fullstack Developer with expertise in JavaScript, TypeScript, React.js, Node.js, CI/CD, npm, yarn, Webpack, and Babel. He has worked as an Administrator Oracle BI Publisher, a Fullstack Developer for Company A, and a Frontend Developer for Company B.
